name: Masha Rasputina
description: '''Masha Rasputina''' (Russian: Маша Распутина, born '''Alla Nikolayevna Ageeva''', Russian: Алла Николаевна Агеева) is a Russian pop singer, who went through her peak of popularity in the 1990s and 2000s. In 2003, she scored her biggest hit, "Roza chaynaya" (Russian: Роза чайная, meaning "Tea rose"), a duet with [[Philipp Kirkorov]].
